    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are looking at a high-ceiling slate today, headlined by **Kyle Schwarber** (77.03) and **Trea Turner** (75.86). Both players benefit from an ideal confluence of variables against Shota Imanaga, including a 4% park boost and wind blowing out at the stadium. **Kyle Schwarber** continues to be an xwOBA anchor for our lineup, while **Trea Turner** remains our primary engine for stolen base production; despite a 4% efficiency penalty against the opponent's elite holding of runners, his lead-off spot and favorable platoon matchup make him an essential play. We are also monitoring **Caleb Durbin** (67.32), who offers a high-value profile today due to a favorable matchup against Luis Gil; his 19% boost from the SP skill profile makes him the third-strongest play in our daily rotation.\n\nThe most difficult bench decision involved **Josh Smith** (48.28), who fell just shy of our marginal start threshold. While his platoon edge against Carmen Mlodzinski was significant (+14%), the combination of a lower-tier batting order position and the overall efficiency of our starting utility slots kept him on the bench. We are also exercising caution with **Hyeseong Kim** (57.15), who carries a 35% rain risk; he remains in the lineup for now, but owners should be prepared for potential in-game weather impacts. Notably, we have benched the high-upside speed of **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (42.58) due to a difficult matchup against Jes\u00fas Luzardo and the associated defensive risks, favoring the safer output profiles of **Victor Scott II** and **Carson Benge** to chase our daily SB targets.",
